<br>
Also if EQ was designed better they would not have the issues they have today.  Having 3 trinity classes required for every group (they are making them required more and more everyday with high hitting, unrootable, unsnareable, summoning mobs) and then 12 other classes to fill the last 3 slots.  For every 3 players of 1 of the 12 other classes you need a trinity set.  That balance just is not there.  Yes in some situation like PoG without protectors you could get away with a Shadowknight/Shaman/Mage group or druid/necro/rogue group, now though you can't which means those people will now be crowding into another zone.  (Raids luckily are different and that ratios of some trinity classes are not so high with the other support classes)<br>
